SIMPLE: awk
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Awk
<hw>Awk</hw> <pr>(⟦add⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>auk</ets>,
<ets>awk</ets> (properly) turned away; (hence) contrary, wrong, from
Icel. <ets>⟦oum⟧figr</ets>, <ets>⟦oum⟧fugr</ets>, <ets>afigr</ets>,
turning the wrong way, fr. <ets>af</ets> off, away; cf. OHG.
<ets>abuh</ets>, Skr. <ets>ap⟦amac⟧c</ets> turned away, fr.
<ets>apa</ets> off, away + a root <ets>ak</ets>, <ets>a⟦ucr⟧k</ets>, to
bend, from which come also E. <ets>angle</ets>,
<ets>anchor</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Odd; out of order; perverse.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wrong, or not commonly used; clumsy; sinister;
<as>as, the <ex>awk</ex> end of a rod (the but end)</as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Golding.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Clumsy in performance or manners; unhandy; not
dexterous; awkward.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Awk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Awk
<hw>Awk</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Perversely; in the wrong way.</def>
<rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Awkly</ent>⟦br⟧
